Important practical effect:

- You may use the API without making the rest of your application open source.
- If you modify files from this `api/` directory and distribute those modified
  files or a program containing them, the modified API files must remain under
  the MPL-2.0 and their source code must be made available to recipients.
- New files outside this API can use a different license unless they copy code
  from MPL-covered API files.

Project contribution policy:

Improvements to the API should be proposed back to the original GfxStack API
repository whenever practical. This keeps the free API healthy and avoids
private forks drifting away. This contribution request is project policy; the
legal license terms are the MPL-2.0.

